# üîç KPI Disclosure and Verification Analysis

## Objective
To evaluate the credibility and auditability of Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) used by transition bond issuers, based on their alignment with science-based frameworks and external assurance.

## Overview
This notebook categorizes each bond's KPIs as externally verified, internally developed, or untraceable. It identifies systemic verification gaps in ESG disclosures and models the distribution of credible vs. non-credible reporting.

## Tools & Methods
- Manual classification in Excel
- Python for grouping, pivoting, and heatmap generation
- Classification logic based on third-party validation, CAPEX timelines, and KPI relevance

